

Student Performance Prediction Using Machine Learning

Introduction:
This project predicts student academic performance using Machine Learning by analyzing study time, attendance, parental education, travel time, and previous academic records. A Streamlit web application provides instant predictions. 


Objectives:

Predict student performance.

Identify key factors affecting performance.

Develop a Streamlit web application.

Demonstrate the use of Machine Learning in education. 


Technologies Used:
Python, Google Colab, Pandas, NumPy, Scikit-learn, Streamlit, Joblib, GitHub. 


Methodology:

Collect and preprocess data.

Train and evaluate the model.

Save the trained model.

Develop the Streamlit application.

Test the application. 


Results:
The model successfully predicts student performance and provides instant results through the web application. 


Conclusion:
This project demonstrates the practical use of Machine Learning in education and can be improved using larger datasets and advanced algorithms. 


Future Scope:

Improve accuracy.

Use real-time datasets.

Integrate with school systems.

Add analytics.

Deploy on the cloud